A guide on installation and usage of PyDGGA.

PyDGGA is a Python implementation of Gradient-based Genetic Algorithm (GGA)
modified to exploit the resources of a distributed computing environment.

1. Download archive
 $ wget http://ulog.udl.cat/download/416/pydgga-1.6.0.zip

2. Unpack pydgga-1.6.0.zip
 $ unzip pydgga-1.6.0.zip

3. Enter directory pydgga-1.6.0
$ cd pydgga-1.6.0

4. Copy the license file to /home/user/ directory
 $ cp pydgga.lic /home/user/.pydgga.lic
 Note: a licence shoould be up to date, otherwise a new license file should be requested.

5. Manual is PyDGGA-Manual.pdf

6. An example of PyDGGA run to optimise Glucose's parameters:
 $ ./pydgga-1.6.0-linux_x86_64 gga -s examples/sat/glucose4
